<TITLE> Islam death probe 'includes bomb experts' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 6 (bdnews24.com)  The investigation into the deaths of Ganotontree Party president Nurul Islam and son Tamohar, after a fire broke out in their home last week, includes the involvement of bomb experts, police say. "Police have filed two unnatural death cases but no official complaint has been made by the family till now, said Dhaka metropolitan police commissioner Nayeem Ahmed. "Investigations are being carried out on the basis of eye-witness accounts, spot evidence and opinions of bomb experts." Asked about any definite proof of the fire being deliberately started, he declined to comment. Tamohar Islam died in the blaze in the early hours of last Wednesday. Islam who suffered critical burns, succumbed to his injuries at Dhaka Combined Military Hospital on Thursday evening. No other members of the family were at home when the fire broke out; Islam's wife and daughter who were in the United States returned home on Thursday night. Police commissioner Nayeem was briefing reporters on security measures over Eid at a press conference on Saturday. bdnew
